{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RWaBrLPBqdmoCjZdVxEu2p","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F14 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC §6.6 — `GET /api/users/[id]`:\n6\t\n7\tReturns:\n8\t```json\n9\t{\n10\t  \"resolved_id\": \"user@example.com\",\n11\t  \"first_seen\": \"...\",\n12\t  \"last_seen\": \"...\",\n13\t  \"identity_cluster\": {\n14\t    \"user_ids\": [\"user@example.com\"],\n15\t    \"device_ids\": [\"device-abc\", \"device-xyz\"]\n16\t  },\n17\t  \"events\": [...]\n18\t}\n19\t```\n20\t\n21\t- Returns a full user profile for a given resolved identity.\n22\t- Includes `resolved_id`, `first_seen`, `last_seen`, `identity_cluster` (user_ids + device_ids), and `events` (reverse chronological, up to 200).\n23\t- Returns 404 when no events are found for the given resolved_id.\n24\t- Returns 500 on internal errors.\n25\t\n26\t## Dependencies\n27\t\n28\tThis feature builds on:\n29\t\n30\t- **F1** — `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` (ClickHouse client singleton)\n31\t- **F4** — `src/lib/identity.ts` (identity resolution logic, `EventRow` type)\n32\t- **F13** — `src/lib/users.ts` (exports `getUserProfile`, `UserProfile` type — already fully implemented)\n33\t- **F13** — `src/app/api/users/route.ts` (sibling route, establishes pattern)\n34\t\n35\tKey imports:\n36\t- `getUserProfile` from `@/lib/users` — already implemented with 3 ClickHouse queries (stats, identity cluster, events)\n37\t- `UserProfile` type from `@/lib/users`\n38\t\n39\t## Files to create or modify\n40\t\n41\t- **CREATE** `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` — the GET route handler\n42\t\n43\tNote: The library function `getUserProfile` in `src/lib/users.ts` already exists and is fully tested (unit tests in `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts`, integration tests in `src/lib/__tests__/users.integration.test.ts`). The route-level unit test at `src/app/api/users/[id]/__tests__/route.test.ts` also already exists and expects the route to export a `GET` function with signature `GET(request: Request, context: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> })`.\n44\t\n45\t## Implementation order\n46\t\n47\t1. **Create `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts`** — implement the `GET` handler:\n48\t   - Extract `id` from `context.params` (awaited Promise).\n49\t   - Call `getUserProfile(id)`.\n50\t   - If result is `null`, return `Response.json({ error: \"User not found.\" }, { status: 404 })`.\n51\t   - On success, return `Response.json(result)` with status 200.\n52\t   - Wrap in try/catch; on error return `Response.json({ error: message }, { status: 500 })`.\n53\t\n54\tThat is the only step — the library logic and all tests are pre-written.\n55\t\n56\t## Sprint contract\n57\t\n58\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` exists and exports a `GET` function\n59\t- [ ] Test suite → 0 failures (`pnpm test`)\n60\t- [ ] Linter → exit 0 (`pnpm lint`)\n61\t- [ ] Type check → exit 0 (`pnpm typecheck`)\n62\t- [ ] Build → exit 0 (`pnpm build`)\n63\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/api/users/nonexistent-id-12345` → response status 404, body contains `\"error\"`\n64\t- [ ] HTTP check: after seeding data via POST `http://localhost:3000/api/seed`, GET `http://localhost:3000/api/users` to find a valid user, then GET `http://localhost:3000/api/users/{resolved_id}` → response status 200, body contains `\"resolved_id\"`, `\"identity_cluster\"`, `\"events\"`\n65\t\n66\t## Test plan\n67\t\n68\tAll tests for F14 are **already written** and ready to validate the implementation:\n69\t\n70\t- **Route unit test**: `src/app/api/users/[id]/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n71\t  - Module under test: `GET` from `@/app/api/users/[id]/route`\n72\t  - Cases covered: returns 200 with full profile shape, passes id to getUserProfile, returns 404 when user not found, returns 500 when getUserProfile throws\n73\t\n74\t- **Library unit test**: `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts`\n75\t  - Module under test: `getUserProfile` from `@/lib/users`\n76\t  - Cases covered: returns profile with all fields, identity_cluster includes associated user_ids/device_ids, returns null when not found\n77\t\n78\t- **Library integration test**: `src/lib/__tests__/users.integration.test.ts`\n79\t  - Module under test: `getUserProfile` from `@/lib/users`\n80\t  - Cases covered: returns null for nonexistent user, returns correct fields when user exists, identity_cluster includes device_ids, events ordered newest first\n81\t\n82\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks against dev server (GET `/api/users/[id]`) — requires running dev server\n83\t\n84\tNo new tests need to be written for this feature.\n85\t\n86\t## Risks and open questions\n87\t\n88\tNone. The `getUserProfile` function is already fully implemented and tested. This feature is a thin route handler that delegates entirely to the library function. The route test is also pre-written, so the implementation is fully constrained by the existing test expectations.\n89\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e8f2076-f971-4e3e-a332-70fda55cefab","uuid":"cfa4d53a-ff19-4700-909c-e3a0f367876c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T14:20:18.643Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F14-plan.md","content":"# F14 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC §6.6 — `GET /api/users/[id]`:\n\nReturns:\n```json\n{\n  \"resolved_id\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"first_seen\": \"...\",\n  \"last_seen\": \"...\",\n  \"identity_cluster\": {\n    \"user_ids\": [\"user@example.com\"],\n    \"device_ids\": [\"device-abc\", \"device-xyz\"]\n  },\n  \"events\": [...]\n}\n```\n\n- Returns a full user profile for a given resolved identity.\n- Includes `resolved_id`, `first_seen`, `last_seen`, `identity_cluster` (user_ids + device_ids), and `events` (reverse chronological, up to 200).\n- Returns 404 when no events are found for the given resolved_id.\n- Returns 500 on internal errors.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis feature builds on:\n\n- **F1** — `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` (ClickHouse client singleton)\n- **F4** — `src/lib/identity.ts` (identity resolution logic, `EventRow` type)\n- **F13** — `src/lib/users.ts` (exports `getUserProfile`, `UserProfile` type — already fully implemented)\n- **F13** — `src/app/api/users/route.ts` (sibling route, establishes pattern)\n\nKey imports:\n- `getUserProfile` from `@/lib/users` — already implemented with 3 ClickHouse queries (stats, identity cluster, events)\n- `UserProfile` type from `@/lib/users`\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- **CREATE** `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` — the GET route handler\n\nNote: The library function `getUserProfile` in `src/lib/users.ts` already exists and is fully tested (unit tests in `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts`, integration tests in `src/lib/__tests__/users.integration.test.ts`). The route-level unit test at `src/app/api/users/[id]/__tests__/route.test.ts` also already exists and expects the route to export a `GET` function with signature `GET(request: Request, context: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> })`.\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts`** — implement the `GET` handler:\n   - Extract `id` from `context.params` (awaited Promise).\n   - Call `getUserProfile(id)`.\n   - If result is `null`, return `Response.json({ error: \"User not found.\" }, { status: 404 })`.\n   - On success, return `Response.json(result)` with status 200.\n   - Wrap in try/catch; on error return `Response.json({ error: message }, { status: 500 })`.\n\nThat is the only step — the library logic and all tests are pre-written.\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] File `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` exists and exports a `GET` function\n- [ ] Test suite → 0 failures (`pnpm test`)\n- [ ] Linter → exit 0 (`pnpm lint`)\n- [ ] Type check → exit 0 (`pnpm typecheck`)\n- [ ] Build → exit 0 (`pnpm build`)\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/api/users/nonexistent-id-12345` → response status 404, body contains `\"error\"`\n- [ ] HTTP check: after seeding data via POST `http://localhost:3000/api/seed`, GET `http://localhost:3000/api/users` to find a valid user, then GET `http://localhost:3000/api/users/{resolved_id}` → response status 200, body contains `\"resolved_id\"`, `\"identity_cluster\"`, `\"events\"`\n\n## Test plan\n\nAll tests for F14 are **already written** and ready to validate the implementation:\n\n- **Route unit test**: `src/app/api/users/[id]/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n  - Module under test: `GET` from `@/app/api/users/[id]/route`\n  - Cases covered: returns 200 with full profile shape, passes id to getUserProfile, returns 404 when user not found, returns 500 when getUserProfile throws\n\n- **Library unit test**: `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts`\n  - Module under test: `getUserProfile` from `@/lib/users`\n  - Cases covered: returns profile with all fields, identity_cluster includes associated user_ids/device_ids, returns null when not found\n\n- **Library integration test**: `src/lib/__tests__/users.integration.test.ts`\n  - Module under test: `getUserProfile` from `@/lib/users`\n  - Cases covered: returns null for nonexistent user, returns correct fields when user exists, identity_cluster includes device_ids, events ordered newest first\n\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP checks against dev server (GET `/api/users/[id]`) — requires running dev server\n\nNo new tests need to be written for this feature.\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\nNone. The `getUserProfile` function is already fully implemented and tested. This feature is a thin route handler that delegates entirely to the library function. The route test is also pre-written, so the implementation is fully constrained by the existing test expectations.\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
